The names of the 11 released Kaduna-Abuja train victims have been released. Terrorists had abducted over 60 train passengers in March 2022 but released the Managing Director of the Bank of Agriculture a few days later. They also released a pregnant woman who was abducted alongside other victims. However, on Saturday 11, 2022, the terrorists released five males and six females whose names were given below;
Amina Ba’aba Mohammed
Rashida Yusuf Busari
Jessey John
Hannah Ajewole
Amina Jibril
Najib Mohammed Dahiru
Hassan Aliyu
Peace A. Boy
Danjuma Sa’idu
Gaius Gambo One other boy whose name was not released was among those released. Publisher of Desert Herald, Tukur Mamu, served as a mediator in the deal that led to their release.